  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Feature 1: Basic Usage â€” Wrap Any Training Loop\n",
    "\n",
    "`GreenTensor` is a context manager. Wrap your existing training code â€” zero changes to the training logic itself.\n",
    "\n",
    "On exit it automatically:\n",
    "- Stops energy/carbon tracking\n",
    "- Reverts GPU optimizations\n",
    "- Prints a full report\n",
    "- Saves `RunMetrics` to a `.pkl` file\n",
    "\n",
    "The `metrics` attribute on the context object gives you programmatic access to all measurements.\n"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "from greentensor import GreenTensor\n",
    "\n",
    "model = make_model()\n",
    "\n",
    "with GreenTensor(verbose=True) as gt:\n",
    "    train_loop(model, n_iters=8)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Programmatic access to metrics\n",
    "m = gt.metrics\n",
    "print(f\"\\nProgrammatic access:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  duration_s   : {m.duration_s:.3f} s\")\n",
    "print(f\"  energy_kwh   : {m.energy_kwh:.6f} kWh\")\n",
    "print(f\"  emissions_kg : {m.emissions_kg:.6f} kg CO2\")\n",
    "print(f\"  idle_seconds : {m.idle_seconds:.2f} s\")"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Decorator variant\n",
    "\n",
    "`GreenTensor.profile` wraps a function instead of a block.\n"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "@GreenTensor.profile\n",
    "def train_fraud_model():\n",
    "    m = make_model()\n",
    "    train_loop(m, n_iters=5)\n",
    "    return m\n",
    "\n",
    "trained_model = train_fraud_model()\n",
    "print(\"Decorator variant complete.\")"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },

  {
