    "## Feature 2: Baseline vs Optimized Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "Pass a `baseline` `RunMetrics` object to GreenTensor and the report automatically shows savings.\n",
    "\n",
    "The `calculate_savings()` utility gives you the delta programmatically â€” useful for CI/CD gates.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Real-world savings from GreenTensor optimizations:**\n",
    "- Mixed precision (FP16): 20â€“40% energy reduction on Tensor Core GPUs\n",
    "- cuDNN benchmark mode: 10â€“30% speedup on CNN workloads\n",
    "- Idle GPU elimination: up to 35% reduction when data pipeline is the bottleneck\n"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "from greentensor import GreenTensor, calculate_savings, RunMetrics\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Run 1: Baseline (no optimizations, verbose=False to keep output clean) ---\n",
    "print(\"Running baseline...\")\n",
    "model_baseline = make_model()\n",
    "with GreenTensor(verbose=False) as gt_baseline:\n",
    "    train_loop(model_baseline, n_iters=8)\n",
    "baseline_metrics = gt_baseline.metrics\n",
    "print(f\"Baseline: {baseline_metrics.energy_kwh:.6f} kWh | {baseline_metrics.duration_s:.3f}s\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Run 2: Optimized (pass baseline for comparison report) ---\n",
    "print(\"\\nRunning optimized (with baseline comparison)...\")\n",
    "model_opt = make_model()\n",
    "with GreenTensor(baseline=baseline_metrics, verbose=True) as gt_opt:\n",
    "    with gt_opt.mixed_precision():\n",
    "        train_loop(model_opt, n_iters=8)\n",
    "optimized_metrics = gt_opt.metrics"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Programmatic savings calculation\n",
    "savings = calculate_savings(baseline_metrics, optimized_metrics)\n",
