  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Feature 5: Carbon Budget Enforcement\n",
    "\n",
    "`CarbonBudget` sets hard limits on CO2 or energy per run. Raises `CarbonBudgetExceeded` if the job goes over.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Use cases:**\n",
    "- CI/CD gate: fail the pipeline if a training run exceeds budget\n",
    "- Cost control: cap energy spend per experiment\n",
    "- ESG compliance: enforce per-project carbon quotas\n",
    "\n",
    "Parameters:\n",
    "- `max_kg_per_run`: hard CO2 limit\n",
    "- `max_kwh_per_run`: hard energy limit\n",
    "- `warn_at_pct`: emit warning at this % of budget (default 80%)\n",
    "- `raise_on_exceed`: if False, just warns instead of raising\n"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "from greentensor import CarbonBudget\n",
    "\n",
    "# Demo: budget that will NOT be exceeded (generous limit)\n",
    "budget_ok = CarbonBudget(\n",
    "    max_kg_per_run=1.0,       # 1 kg CO2 â€” very generous\n",
    "    warn_at_pct=80.0,\n",
    "    job_name=\"fraud-detector-v1\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "model = make_model()\n",
    "with GreenTensor(verbose=False) as gt:\n",
    "    train_loop(model, n_iters=8)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Manually check budget after run\n",
    "budget_ok.check(gt.metrics.emissions_kg, gt.metrics.energy_kwh)\n",
    "print(f\"Budget check passed.\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Used: {gt.metrics.emissions_kg:.6f} kg / {budget_ok.max_kg_per_run} kg budget\")\n",
    "print(f\"  ({gt.metrics.emissions_kg / budget_ok.max_kg_per_run * 100:.4f}% of budget consumed)\")"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "from greentensor import CarbonBudgetExceeded\n",
    "\n",
    "# Demo: budget that WILL be exceeded (tiny limit to trigger the exception)\n",
    "budget_tight = CarbonBudget(\n",
    "    max_kg_per_run=0.000000001,  # 1 nanogram â€” will always exceed\n",
    "    warn_at_pct=50.0,\n",
    "    raise_on_exceed=True,\n",
    "    job_name=\"fraud-detector-v2\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    budget_tight.check(\n",
