    "## Feature 8: Carbon Anomaly Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "`AnomalyDetector` continuously monitors GPU power draw using statistical anomaly detection.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Two detection engines:**\n",
    "1. **alibi-detect SpectralResidual** â€” frequency-domain statistical outlier detection (same algorithm as Microsoft Azure Metrics Advisor). Requires `pip install alibi-detect`.\n",
    "2. **Threshold detector** â€” fallback when alibi-detect is unavailable. Fires when power exceeds baseline by `spike_threshold_pct`.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Attack patterns detected:**\n",
    "- `power_spike` â€” sudden energy surge (cryptominer injection)\n",
    "- `sustained_overload` â€” prolonged above-baseline usage (data exfiltration)\n",
    "- `idle_drain` â€” GPU power draw while idle (hidden background process)\n",
    "- `prompt_injection` â€” adversarial inputs (via LLM Guard)\n",
    "- `data_leakage` â€” sensitive data in model outputs (via LLM Guard)\n"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "from greentensor import AnomalyDetector, AnomalyDetectorConfig, AnomalyAlert\n",
    "\n",
    "# Collect alerts in a list\n",
    "alerts_received = []\n",
    "\n",
    "def my_alert_handler(alert: AnomalyAlert):\n",
    "    alerts_received.append(alert)\n",
    "    print(f\"  [ALERT/{alert.severity.upper()}] [{alert.source}] {alert.alert_type}: {alert.message[:80]}...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configure detector\n",
    "config = AnomalyDetectorConfig(\n",
    "    baseline_window=30,\n",
    "    sample_interval_s=0.5,\n",
    "    spike_threshold_pct=80.0,\n",
    "    idle_drain_threshold_w=50.0,\n",
    "    consecutive_anomalies_required=2,\n",
    "    use_alibi_detect=True,   # will fall back to threshold if not installed\n",
    "    use_llm_guard=False,     # skip LLM Guard for this demo\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "detector = AnomalyDetector(config=config, on_alert=my_alert_handler)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use as context manager\n",
    "with detector:\n",
    "    model = make_model()\n",
    "    train_loop(model, n_iters=8)\n",
    "    time.sleep(0.5)  # let the monitor sample a few times\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nMonitoring complete. Total alerts: {len(alerts_received)}\")\n",
    "if not alerts_received:\n",
    "    print(\"  Status: CLEAN â€” no anomalies detected during training.\")"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
