    "When a carbon/power spike is detected, `PatternMatcher` immediately correlates it with digital footprint signals to determine if it's a cyberattack or a benign event.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Scoring logic:**\n",
    "- Each active signal adds a weighted score toward a specific attack type\n",
    "- Benign context signals (checkpoint saving, eval loop, warmup) reduce the score\n",
    "- Score 0â€“49: BENIGN | 50â€“79: SUSPICIOUS | 80â€“100: ATTACK\n",
    "\n",
    "**Attack patterns:**\n",
    "- `cryptominer`: power spike + new process + high GPU util + no training activity\n",
    "- `data_exfiltration`: idle drain + outbound network + low util\n",
    "- `backdoor_trigger`: inference latency spike + high confidence + brief power spike\n",
    "- `model_theft`: high-frequency probing + systematic inputs + outbound network\n"
   ],
